content.shortDescription: Taking place during the events of John Wick: Chapter 3 – Parabellum, Eve Macarro begins her training in the assassin traditions of the Ruska Roma.
content.title: Ballerina

textRecommendations.headline: Ballerina shows that John Wick can survive without Keanu Reeves
textRecommendations.body: While viewers may think that John Wick can only work if Keanu Reeves is involved, Ballerina shows that the series can still succeed without him. The action is still top-tier and features plenty of excellent practical effects and stuntwork that deliver all the thrills you would expect from a John Wick movie. It's undeniably slower, but Ballerina uses that methodical pace to flesh out several aspects of its already complex world. Even if it may not reach the lofty heights of earlier entries, Ballerina is still an impressive action film that fans of the genre will eat up.

profile.bio:
Jesse Lab is a lover of all things entertainment, from film, to anime, to video games, and comics, if there's something nerdy, Jesse probably knows about it. He has been writing professionally since 2018.

Experience and Education

Jesse serves as the Features Editor of the film site Flixist, where he covers events like the Tribeca Film Festival and conventions. He also contributes to the video game websites The Escapist and SavePoint Gaming.Jesse is a graduate of Fairleigh Dickenson University, where he earned his Master's in Secondary Education, a BA in History, and a BA in Theater Arts with a concentration in acting.

Favourite Movies and TV-Shows

Jesse is a fan of all genres of film and television, with some of his favorite films being Who Framed Roger Rabbit? (Robert Zemeckis), The Thing (John Carpenter), and Everything Everywhere All At Once (The Daniels). Some of his favorite TV and anime include Hannibal, Scrubs, Gankutsuou: The Count of Monte Cristo, and Mob Psycho 100.

textRecommendations.headline: The ultimate proof Ana de Armas is a movie star
textRecommendations.body: Ballerina is a fun action movie that gets carried over the finish line by Ana de Armas. Happening alongside the events of the third John Wick, Ballerina focuses on another wildcard in this world of assassins and bodyguards named Eve. Chasing after the cult that took her family, Eve spends almost the entire movie in some form of fight or chase. It's an exciting film with a strong balance of hard-hitting violence, clever kills, and absurd beats. While the plot isn't always the strongest, de Armas' sheer charm and talent for stunt work makes this a definite must-watch for action fans.

profile.bio:
Based in Los Angeles, Brandon Zachary is a seasoned entertainment journalist, award-nominated screenwriter, and massive nerd.

Experience and Education

Brandon graduated from Columbia College with a BA in Cinematic Arts & Sciences before becoming a staple at some of the most popular pop culture institutions in the world. You may have seen his work as Contributing Writer with TVBrittanyF and That Hashtag Show, as a Senior Writer at CBR.com or his work at ScreenRant, where he also served as Senior Writer and Editor.

Favorite Movies and TV Shows

As is true with his background, Brandon's tastes are both varied and sundry. When it comes to the big screen, he loves everything from Shaun of the Dead, and Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse to City Lights, Rear Window, and The Shining. When it comes to TV, you can usually read his musings about The Simpsons, Spaced, The Good Place, The Venture Brothers, and The Twilight Zone
